          "display_name": null,
          "email": "anjali.walsatwar@huawei.com",
          "username": "AnjaliW"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-11-20 05:16:04.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 11:\n\n> Hi,\n > \n > I have a question regarding the design.\n > In a scenario in which I copy an instance and then not immediately\n > pasting it instead I continue working in the composition tab and\n > after a while I want to paste it, or even the opposite. I\n > accidentally paste it, I don't have any visual sign of which\n > instance has been copied.\n > In more complex situation this could be a problem for the user.\n > Is this something that is resolvable?\n > Adding some kind of visual representation of the copied instance?\n\n1. if user is copy any instance it will be for paste purpose\n2. even if user just copied instance and latter it got pasted by mistake,it can be always deleted\n3. please suggest where can we add this visual representation of copied instance,can we always show border around copied instance(but border is for selected instance) unless other instance is not copied or pasted.",
        "patchset_number": 11
      },
